01 Create App with User Auth
----------------------------

1. Create app with default db (mysql)
	NOTE: Using laragon
	> pmanager
	Open it in the browser
	> pmanager.test :)
	> commit to git

2. Pust it to Github
	> create a new repository
	> git remote add origin git@github.com:ingafter60/pmanager.git
	Create SSH Key
	> cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
	...
	Use the created SSH key to create SSH Key
	> git push -u origin master
	...
	Refresh the browser and check the result :)

3. Create User with Authentication
	Create a new git branch
	> git checkout -b 1_CreateUserwithAuth
	> Create db: pmanager
	> php artisan make:auth
	> php artisan migrate
	> Register a new user
	> Testing: logout, then login :)

4. Push to Github
	> git add .
	> git commit
	> git push origin	1_CreateUserwithAuth

5. Merging the branches
	> git checkout master
	NOTE: make sure you are in the master branch
	> I:\laragon\www\pmanager (master)
	> Î» git merge 1_CreateUserwithAuth

